	(6072, 'facebook198744036811672_1079282632091137', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1079282632091137', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1079282632091137/picture?type=normal', 'Q: Today, the top takes on the bottom as you receive Toulouse FC who is in 19th place in Ligue 1, second to last. What are your thoughts about the match?\n\nZlatan: 3 points.\n\nQ:Toulouse is well-known for being a rough team that often is shown the referee’s red card. How does this affect a skillful team like PSG who often dominate the matches?\n\nZlatan: We focus on our game.\n\nQ: Do you still feel the stubborn cold that has been tormenting you the last few weeks?\n\nZlatan: Yes, I still feel it.\n\nQ: Danish national Martin Braithwaite is on the opposing team. He is keen scorer in Toulouse, and is also part of the national squad that will meet Sweden in the Euro playoffs. Do you see Braithwaite as at threat to PSG – or a threat to Sweden in the playoff matches?\n\nZlatan: He is a good player.', '', 'en', 'Q: Today, the top takes on the bottom as you receive Toulouse FC who is in 19th place in Ligue 1, second to last. What are your thoughts about the match?\n\nZlatan: 3 points.\n\nQ:Toulouse is well-known for being a rough team that often is shown the referee’s red card. How does this affect a skillful team like PSG who often dominate the matches?\n\nZlatan: We focus on our game.\n\nQ: Do you still feel the stubborn cold that has been tormenting you the last few weeks?\n\nZlatan: Yes, I still feel it.\n\nQ: Danish national Martin Braithwaite is on the opposing team. He is keen scorer in Toulouse, and is also part of the national squad that will meet Sweden in the Euro playoffs. Do you see Braithwaite as at threat to PSG – or a threat to Sweden in the playoff matches?\n\nZlatan: He is a good player.', '2015-11-07 11:18:58', 205),
	(6073, 'facebook198744036811672_1078430768842990', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1078430768842990', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1078430768842990/picture?type=normal', 'Introducing the new home jersey for Sweden. Looking forward to be wearing the new kit when I step on to the pitch and lead our country in the battle for a place at the Euro 2016. #BeTheDifference', '', 'en', 'Introducing the new home jersey for Sweden. Looking forward to be wearing the new kit when I step on to the pitch and lead our country in the battle for a place at the Euro 2016. #BeTheDifference', '2015-11-05 09:10:45', 247),
	(6074, 'facebook198744036811672_1077703592249041', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1077703592249041', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1077703592249041/picture?type=normal', 'Q: Tonight, you meet Real Madrid again, this time at Santiago Bernabéu in Madrid. The first match ended 0-0 after 90 cautious minutes where no one wanted to risk too much. Do you expect a similar match tonight?\n\nZlatan: It will be a completely different match tonight at Bernabéu.\n\nQ: In PSG’s last match, a 1-0 win against Rennes, you sat on the bench the whole match due to a stubborn cold. How do you feel today?\n\nZlatan: It feels a little better today.\n\nQ: In regards to this match, team captain Thiago Silva have said that this will be a tough match but you go to Madrid to win, and that you have a good chance to do so. Do you see PSG and Real Madrid as two equal teams, or does Project PSG still have a bit left to go?\n\nZlatan: PSG is still in the up-phase, while Real Madrid already has their team in place.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '', 'en', 'Q: Tonight, you meet Real Madrid again, this time at Santiago Bernabéu in Madrid. The first match ended 0-0 after 90 cautious minutes where no one wanted to risk too much. Do you expect a similar match tonight?\n\nZlatan: It will be a completely different match tonight at Bernabéu.\n\nQ: In PSG’s last match, a 1-0 win against Rennes, you sat on the bench the whole match due to a stubborn cold. How do you feel today?\n\nZlatan: It feels a little better today.\n\nQ: In regards to this match, team captain Thiago Silva have said that this will be a tough match but you go to Madrid to win, and that you have a good chance to do so. Do you see PSG and Real Madrid as two equal teams, or does Project PSG still have a bit left to go?\n\nZlatan: PSG is still in the up-phase, while Real Madrid already has their team in place.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '2015-11-03 17:05:08', 257),
	(6075, 'facebook198744036811672_1075934399092627', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1075934399092627', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1075934399092627/picture?type=normal', 'Q: Tonight you face Rennes away, who at the moment is in seventh place in the league. What are your thoughts about the match?\n\nZlatan: It’s usually hard to meet Rennes away. \n\nQ: You were substituted in the 70th minute of your last match due to a cold and fever. How do you feel today?\n\nZlatan: It’s still there.\n\nQ: Just four days after the match against Rennes you meet Real Madrid away. How will this affect your performance and lineup?\n\nZlatan: We need to do our job anyway. Our coach decides the lineup. \n\nQ: Looking statistically at your season it’s evident that it’s in the last fifteen minutes of the matches that you concede the most goals. On the other hand, it’s also during this time you score the most goals by far. How come your scoring average increases so drastically in the last quarter?\n\nZlatan: I have no idea, but it’s nothing we think about anyway.', '', 'en', 'Q: Tonight you face Rennes away, who at the moment is in seventh place in the league. What are your thoughts about the match?\n\nZlatan: It’s usually hard to meet Rennes away. \n\nQ: You were substituted in the 70th minute of your last match due to a cold and fever. How do you feel today?\n\nZlatan: It’s still there.\n\nQ: Just four days after the match against Rennes you meet Real Madrid away. How will this affect your performance and lineup?\n\nZlatan: We need to do our job anyway. Our coach decides the lineup. \n\nQ: Looking statistically at your season it’s evident that it’s in the last fifteen minutes of the matches that you concede the most goals. On the other hand, it’s also during this time you score the most goals by far. How come your scoring average increases so drastically in the last quarter?\n\nZlatan: I have no idea, but it’s nothing we think about anyway.', '2015-10-30 15:57:33', 289),
	(6076, 'facebook198744036811672_1073810182638382', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1073810182638382', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1073810182638382/picture?type=normal', 'Q: Tonight you close the 11th round of Ligue 1 as you receive AS Saint-Etienne. The two last meetings with ASSE have ended in comfortable PSG wins, 4-1 and 5-0. What are your thoughts about the match?\n\nZlatan: It will be a good match against one of the favorites to win the league. \n\nQ: The match against Saint-Etienne is your third match in eight days. What is the physical status of team?\n\nZlatan: Very good.\n\nQ: The kickoff is quite late and the referee Clément Turpin doesn’t give the start signal at Parc des Princes until 21.00. How much are you affected by what time the match is played – and at what time do you prefer to play?\n\nZlatan: It doesn’t matter. I’m ready no matter what. \n\nQ: In both of you previous matches against AS Saint-Etienne you have made a hat trick. Are there certain teams you feel better meeting – and in that case is Saint-Etienne one of them?\n\nZlatan: As long as we win I feel good.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '', 'en', 'Q: Tonight you close the 11th round of Ligue 1 as you receive AS Saint-Etienne. The two last meetings with ASSE have ended in comfortable PSG wins, 4-1 and 5-0. What are your thoughts about the match?\n\nZlatan: It will be a good match against one of the favorites to win the league. \n\nQ: The match against Saint-Etienne is your third match in eight days. What is the physical status of team?\n\nZlatan: Very good.\n\nQ: The kickoff is quite late and the referee Clément Turpin doesn’t give the start signal at Parc des Princes until 21.00. How much are you affected by what time the match is played – and at what time do you prefer to play?\n\nZlatan: It doesn’t matter. I’m ready no matter what. \n\nQ: In both of you previous matches against AS Saint-Etienne you have made a hat trick. Are there certain teams you feel better meeting – and in that case is Saint-Etienne one of them?\n\nZlatan: As long as we win I feel good.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '2015-10-25 14:44:35', 324),
	(6077, 'facebook198744036811672_1072148022804598', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1072148022804598', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1072148022804598/picture?type=normal', 'Q: Tonight, two giants clash as your PSG takes on Real Madrid. What kind of match do you anticipate – and who would you say are favourites?\n\nZlatan: Real are probably favorites. But it will be a tough match.\n\nQ: FIFA presented 23 players that are nominated for Ballon d’Or. From PSG one player is nominated, a certain Zlatan Ibrahimovic. From Real Madrid no less than five players have made the list, among them the title-holder Cristiano Ronaldo. What do you think of the nominations and who would you say is favourite to win the title this year?\n\nZlatan: Neither the nominations, nor who wins is anything I think about at all. \n\nQ: Carlo Ancelotti, previous coach for both Paris Saint-Germain and Real Madrid has said that he sees a lot of similarities between you and Cristiano Ronaldo when it comes to professionalism and the will to win. Do you see any similarities between yourself and Real Madrid’s star player?\n\nZlatan: I don’t know him that way, but on the pitch we are two different players.\n\nQ: You have decided big matches against Real Madrid before. What do you think about repeating El Clásico 2009 – 1-0 for the home team with Ibrahimovic as the only scorer?\n\nZlatan: That would be great!\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '', 'en', 'Q: Tonight, two giants clash as your PSG takes on Real Madrid. What kind of match do you anticipate – and who would you say are favourites?\n\nZlatan: Real are probably favorites. But it will be a tough match.\n\nQ: FIFA presented 23 players that are nominated for Ballon d’Or. From PSG one player is nominated, a certain Zlatan Ibrahimovic. From Real Madrid no less than five players have made the list, among them the title-holder Cristiano Ronaldo. Wha