	(6078, 'facebook198744036811672_1070306952988705', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1070306952988705', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1070306952988705/picture?type=normal', 'Q: You’re back in France after winning two matches with the Swedish national team and securing a place in the Euro playoff. Are you happy with what you and Sweden have achieved during the break?\n\nZlatan: Yes. I’m happy with both matches that we played. \n\nQ: David Luiz, Marco Verratti, and Kevin Trapp all got injured during the break and won’t be playing against Bastia. Which players will be key in their absence?\n\nZlatan: There are many players that can play in their positions. \n\nQ: You lead the league with five points and so far you haven’t lost a match. Is the quality of Ligue 1 to low this year to really present a challenge to PSG?\n\nZlatan: We have started well compared to previous seasons. \n\nQ: You are gaining on Edinson Cavani on the top-scorer table. Now you’re just two goals behind your teammate. Is it a prestigious fight between you two – and who will be the top-scorer of Ligue 1 in the end?\n\nZlatan: No no. It’s both our jobs to score goals and help the team. At the end of the day it’s all about winning.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '', 'en', 'Q: You’re back in France after winning two matches with the Swedish national team and securing a place in the Euro playoff. Are you happy with what you and Sweden have achieved during the break?\n\nZlatan: Yes. I’m happy with both matches that we played. \n\nQ: David Luiz, Marco Verratti, and Kevin Trapp all got injured during the break and won’t be playing against Bastia. Which players will be key in their absence?\n\nZlatan: There are many players that can play in their positions. \n\nQ: You lead the league with five points and so far you haven’t lost a match. Is the quality of Ligue 1 to low this year to really present a 