nd whether you will be able to play the game. How do you feel physically?\n\nZlatan: I feel really good.\n\nQ: It looks like you will go on to playoff if you beat Moldova. A deciding double meeting where you could face one of our neighboring countries, Norway or Denmark. Is there an opponent you would prefer in the playoff?\n\nZlatan: A nation I havent met before.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '2015-10-12 13:26:19', 392),
	(6081, 'facebook198744036811672_1067997016553032', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1067997016553032', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1067997016553032/picture?type=normal', 'My Gold Record Award for 3 000 000 Swedish streams of my version of the National anthem. Rumour has it that it’s the most streamed national anthem ever… Either way, it’s pretty cool.', '', 'en', 'My Gold Record Award for 3 000 000 Swedish streams of my version of the National anthem. Rumour has it that it’s the most streamed national anthem ever… Either way, it’s pretty cool.', '2015-10-12 10:39:27', 393),
	(6082, 'facebook198744036811672_1066721993347201', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1066721993347201', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1066721993347201/picture?type=normal', 'Q: In the match against Liechtenstein Sweden will be the dominating team. Is it always an advantage to have that role?\n\nZlatan: That’s what happens automatically when you are the better team. But we have to handle it the right way. \n\nQ: After two heavy losses you are up against Liechtenstein tomorrow. Besides avoiding the mistakes from previous matches, will there be any tactical changes?\n\nZlatan: We don’t know yet. We will have to wait and see. \n\nQ: At team practice you played a match where Skåne met the rest of Sweden. Is it a prestigious fight?\n\nZlatan: Yes!', '', 'en', 'Q: In the match against Liechtenstein Sweden will be the dominating team. Is it always an advantage to have that role?\n\nZlatan: That’s what happens automatically when you are the better team. But we have to handle it the right way. \n\nQ: After two heavy losses you are up against Liechtenstein tomorrow. Besides avoiding the mistakes from previous matches, will there be any tactical changes?\n\nZlatan: We don’t know yet. We will have to wait and see. \n\nQ: At team practice you played a match where Skåne met the rest of Sweden. Is it a prestigious fight?\n\nZlatan: Yes!', '2015-10-09 14:21:34', 402),
	(6083, 'facebook198744036811672_1064950970190970', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1064950970190970', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1064950970190970/picture?type=normal', 'Q: After the two goals, your 109th and 110th for the club, we can now securely congratulate you on being PSG’s all-time leading scorer. How does it feel to have reached this legendary status in Paris Saint-Germain? \n\nZlatan: It feels magical – amazing.\n\nQ: Yesterday you said that it would be really memorable to beat the scoring record by deciding Le Classique. Now you scored the two winning goals and also became the player to have scored the most goals in Le Classique matches ever. Is it the big matches that bring out the best in you? \n\nZlatan: It feels good when there is some nerve in the match.\n\nQ With the scoring record you put your name in the Parisian history books, what is the next record to beat?\n\nZlatan: It remains to be seen.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '', 'en', 'Q: After the two goals, your 109th and 110th for the club, we can now securely congratulate you on being PSG’s all-time leading scorer. How does it feel to have reached this legendary status in Paris Saint-Germain? \n\nZlatan: It feels magical – amazing.\n\nQ: Yesterday you said that it would be really memorable to beat the scoring record by deciding Le Classique. Now you scored the two winning goals and also became the player to have scored the most goals in Le Classique matches ever. Is it the big matches that bring out the best in you? \n\nZlatan: It feels good when there is some nerve in the match.\n\nQ With the scoring record you put your name in the Parisian history books, what is the next record to beat?\n\nZlatan: It remains to be seen.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '2015-10-05 09:14:03', 423),
	(6084, 'facebook198744036811672_1064638080222259', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1064638080222259', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1064638080222259/picture?type=normal', 'Q: Tonight, France’s two biggest cities and football clubs meet in the classic bout Le Classique. Have the matches against Marseille become more important to you now that Paris has become more and more important to you?\n\nZlatan: The way I see it, it is just a regular match just like the other league matches. \n\nQ: The hunt for your 109th goal for PSG continues, a goal that would make you historic as the French capital’s best scorer of all time. How about beating the record by deciding Le Classique tomorrow?\n\nZlatan: That would be really memorable.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '', 'en', 'Q: Tonight, France’s two biggest cities and football clubs meet in the classic bout Le Classique. Have the matches against Marseille become more important to you now that Paris has become more and more important to you?\n\nZlatan: The way I see it, it is just a regular match just like the other league matches. \n\nQ: The hunt for your 109th goal for PSG continues, a goal that would make you historic as the French capital’s best scorer of all time. How about beating the record by deciding Le Classique tomorrow?\n\nZlatan: That would be really memorable.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '2015-10-04 15:42:36', 430),
	(6085, 'facebook198744036811672_1062940830391984', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1062940830391984', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1062940830391984/picture?type=normal', 'Q: Tonight the group stage in the Champions League continues and you go up against the Ukrainian team Shakhtar Donetsk. What do you know about your opponent?\n\nZlatan: We have gone over their team. A very good opponent we will have to look out for. \n\nQ: Due to the unrest in Donetsk the match will be played at Arena Lviv, almost 1 200 kilometers from Shaktar’s real home-arena. How do you think it affects a team to be forced to play their home-matches on a completely different arena in another city?\n\nZlatan: Playing at home is always an advantage, but I don’t know really what the situation is here. \n\nQ: In the opposing team there are many skillful Brazilians like Alex Teixeira, Taison and Bernard, but they lost big in the first match against Real Madrid. If you were to rank the teams in Group A, where do you place Shakhtar and where do you place PSG?\n\nZlatan: There are no places now, the only thing that counts is to take all three points and go through from the group stage.\n\nQ: Focusing on you and PSG instead, how is the form?\n\nZlatan: It feels really good.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '', 'en', 'Q: Tonight the group stage in the Champions League continues and you go up against the Ukrainian team Shakhtar Donetsk. What do you know about your opponent?\n\nZlatan: We have gone over their team. A very good opponent we will have to look out for. \n\nQ: Due to the unrest in Donetsk the match will be played at Arena Lviv, almost 1 200 kilometers from Shaktar’s real home-arena. How do you think it affects a team to be forced to play their home-matches on a completely different arena in another city?\n\nZlatan: Playing at home is always an advantage, but I don’t know really what the situation is here. \n\nQ: In the opposing team there are many skillful Brazilians like Alex Teixeira, Taison and Bernard, but they lost big in the first match against Real Madrid. If you were to rank the teams in Group A, where do you place Shakhtar and where do you place PSG?\n\nZlatan: There are no places now, the only thing that counts is to take all three points and go through from the group stage.\n\nQ: Focusing on you and PSG instead, how is the form?\n\nZlatan: It feels really good.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '2015-09-30 17:00:23', 440),
	(6086, 'facebook198744036811672_1061187673900633', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1061187673900633', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1061187673900633/picture?type=normal', 'Q_: Ligue 1 continues as PSG goes up against Nantes away. Nantes is in seventh place and not a direct threat in the fight for the league title. Which teams do you see as the biggest threats to PSG becoming French champions once more?\n\nZlatan: That would be the same teams as last year.\n\nYou keep chasing Pauleta’s record as the greatest PSG scorer of all times. As of right now you have scored 107, just 2 goals from Pauleta’s 109. When do you beat the record?\n\nZlatan: As soon as possible.\n\nWhat would it mean to you to have scored the most goals in club history?\n\nZlatan: It’s always fun to beat a record.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '', 'en', 'Q_: Ligue 1 continues as PSG goes up against Nantes away. Nantes is in seventh place and not a direct threat in the fight for the league title. Which teams do you see as the biggest threats to PSG becoming French champions once more?\n\nZlatan: That would be the same teams as last year.\n\nYou keep chasing Pauleta’s record as the greatest PSG scorer of all times. As of right now you have scored 107, just 2 goals from Pauleta’s 109. When do you beat the record?\n\nZlatan: As soon as possible.\n\nWhat would it mean to you to have scored the most goals in club history?\n\nZlatan: It’s always fun to beat a record.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '2015-09-26 11:52:03', 456),
	(6087, 'facebook198744036811672_1059762914043109', 'Zlatan Ibrahimovic', 'https://graph.facebook.com/198744036811672/picture?type=normal', 'facebook', 'https://www.facebook.com/198744036811672/posts/1059762914043109', 'https://graph.facebook.com/1059762914043109/picture?type=normal', 'Q: After the away draw this weekend, Guingamp awaits at Parc des Princes tonight\nEight-placed Guingamp comes to Paris with three straight wins. PSG has two draws in the league. What can you do better to take all three points? \n\nZlatan: We are going to play better and dominate more. \n\nQ: PSG is undefeated this season and is expected to win every match, which you didn’t in the last two matches. How does it affect your self-confidence that you didn’t score on your chances in these two matches? \n\nZlatan: Not at all really. These things happen. It’s important to create the chances. \n\nQ: From now on the match schedule is packed with league matches against Guingamp and Nantes, a Champions League match away against Shakthar Donetsk, and Le Classique against Marseille. Do you feel physically fit to play 90 minutes in these matches? \n\nZlatan: It feels better and better – but I’m ready.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '', 'en', 'Q: After the away draw this weekend, Guingamp awaits at Parc des Princes tonight\nEight-placed Guingamp comes to Paris with three straight wins. PSG has two draws in the league. What can you do better to take all three points? \n\nZlatan: We are going to play better and dominate more. \n\nQ: PSG is undefeated this season and is expected to win every match, which you didn’t in the last two matches. How does it affect your self-confidence that you didn’t score on your chances in these two matches? \n\nZlatan: Not at all really. These things happen. It’s important to create the chances. \n\nQ: From now on the match schedule is packed with league matches against Guingamp and Nantes, a Champions League match away against Shakthar Donetsk, and Le Classique against Marseille. Do you feel physically fit to play 90 minutes in these matches? \n\nZlatan: It feels better and better – but I’m ready.\n\nwww.zlatanunplugged.com', '2015-09-22 18:43:19', 475),
