	(7638, 'goal_en17109022', 'Koscielny fit to start north London derby', '', 'goal', 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/1862/premier-league/2015/11/08/17109022/koscielny-fit-to-start-north-london-derby', 'http://static.goal.com/2133500/2133562_heroa.jpg', 'The France defender was a though to be a doubt, with Joel Campbell also starting for the Gunners, while Spurs remain unchanged from their win over Aston Villa', 'Premier League,Arsenal,Tottenham Hotspur', 'en', 'The France defender was a though to be a doubt, with Joel Campbell also starting for the Gunners, while Spurs remain unchanged from their win over Aston Villa  : Cech, Debuchy, Mertesacker, Koscielny, Monreal, Coquelin, Cazorla, Campbell, Ozil, Sanchez, Giroud.  :    \n \n \n \n  defender   will start the north London derby against   despite being an injury doubt for Sundays clash. Manager Arsene Wenger had previously refused to confirm whether Koscielny would be available to start, having missed the embarassing defeat to Bayern Munich in the Champions League, but the France defender partners Per Mertesacker at the back.  Further forward, Olivier Giroud starts up-front with in-from Mesut Ozil in behind and the wide pair of Joel Campbell and Alexis Sanchez playing a supporting role.  Mauricio Pochettinos Tottenham, meanwhile, are unchanged from their Premier League win over Aston Villa, with recent England call-up Eric Dier partnering Dele Alli in midfield and Harry Kane leading the line.  \r\n \n \n Lloris; Walker, Alderweireld, Vertonghen, Rose; Dier, Alli; Lamela, Dembele, Eriksen; Kane. ', '2015-11-08 15:10:00', 6),
	(7641, 'goal_en2039356', 'Feyenoord 1-1 Ajax: Klassen rescues draw for visitors ', '', 'goal', 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/1686/eredivisie/2015/11/08/17107092/feyenoord-1-1-ajax-klassen-rescues-draw-for-visitors', 'http://static.goal.com/2213300/2213312_heroa.jpg', 'The Netherlands international was lucky to see a shot deflected into the net to earn a point for his side after Sven van Beek had opened the scoring for the hosts', 'Eredivisie,Feyenoord,Ajax', 'en', 'The Netherlands international was lucky to see a shot deflected into the net to earn a point for his side after Sven van Beek had opened the scoring for the hosts \n \n \nDavy Klaassen rescued a point for Ajax in Sundays derby match against Feyenoord to ensure his side stay clear at top of the Eredivisie. The clash in De Kuip gave Giovanni van Bronckhorsts men the chance to pull level with their fierce rivals at the top of the table and they looked on course to do so after Sven van Beeks first half strike gave them the lead. However, Klaassen was able to count on a massive deflection to send the ball looping over Kenneth Vermeer to tie the game up. Ajax now sit two points clear of reigning champions PSV, while Feyenoord remain a further point behind Frank de Boers men. Fans at De Kuip were treated to a bright start as both sides pressed forward in search of the breakthrough, though chances were scarce with the first 20 minutes seeing just one attempt on goal.  The game did liven up after that, however, and Feyenoord winger Eljero Elia was the first player to call a goalkeeper into action as Rick Karsdorp’s pass from the right side found its way through to the Netherlands international, but Jasper Cillessen was there to block his effort. Daley Sinkgraven had an even better chance to put Ajax in the lead shortly afterwards when Klaassen knocked a cross down to him inside the box, only to see the ex-Heerenveen star’s shot miss the target. The deadlock was finally broken after 38 minutes when Dirk Kuyt latched onto a pass and drove toward the Ajax box. The 35-year-old then cut it back from the byline where centre-back   was found in open space and was able to slot it in. Nemanja Gudelj tested the home side’s goalkeeper Kenneth Vermeer with a dangerous free kick but the ex-Ajax player was able to palm it over. Joel Veltman had a chance from the subsequent corner, but his header flew too high. The visitors found their equaliser in their very next attack, though, as  ’s shot from the edge of the box struck Terence Kongolo and bounced over Vermeer. As tje game wore on, Ajax were the only side putting any real pressure on their opponents but struggled to make the difference. Substitute Colin Kazim-Richards should have made De Boers side pay for their profligacy as he was sent through on goal, but Cillessen did well to stop his shot. The goalkeeper was required again in injury time as Kuyt sent a header towards goal, but it was an easy one to catch. It proved to be a crucial moment of the game as neither side were able to threaten afterwards, settling for a point. \n', '2015-11-08 15:23:00', 5),
	(7643, 'goal_en2120492', 'Player Ratings: Roma 2-0 Lazio', '', 'goal', 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/1127/player-ratings/2015/11/08/17107482/player-ratings-roma-2-0-lazio', '', 'A dominant Roma saw off Lazio thanks to an insurance goal from Gervinho, but Dzekos controversial penalty opened the scoring', '', 'en', '', '2015-11-08 15:45:00', 4),
	(7646, 'goal_en2120682', 'Roma 2-0 Lazio: Dzeko and Gervinho seal derby win for Giallorossi ', '', 'goal', 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/723/serie-a/2015/11/08/17103202/roma-2-0-lazio-dzeko-and-gervinho-seal-derby-win-for', 'http://static.goal.com/2213400/2213472_heroa.jpg', 'Rudi Garcias side ran out comfortable winners in the Rome derby with goals from former Premier League stars, while Felipe Anderson hit the woodwork', 'Serie A,International Champions Cup,Roma,Lazio', 'en', 'Rudi Garcias side ran out comfortable winners in the Rome derby with goals from former Premier League stars, while Felipe Anderson hit the woodwork \n \n \n  ran out 2-0 winners over fierce city rivals   thanks to goals from   and   either side of half-time, taking the Giallorossi to second in the scudetto race, behind  . Dzeko, a summer signing from Manchester City, was awarded a penalty in controversial circumstances after 10 minutes after a foul from Santiago Gentiletti. Both Felipe Anderson and Radja Nainggolan then rattled the woodwork in the first-half but it took until after the break for the game to be decided, with a brilliant individual goal from Gervinho, leaving Lazio right-back Dusan Batsa in his wake and finding the net.  One of the main points of discussion coming into the usually boisterous Rome Derby was the lack of fans in either the Curva Nord or the Curva Sud, with both Roma and Lazio Ultras deciding to stay away from the Stadio Olimpico in protest against the increased safety measures brought in by the Rome city authorities.   Against that muted backdrop, the game appeared a little flat in spells as the players did not have the roar of the expectant curvas to push them on.    Despite the strange derby atmosphere, Rudi Garcia’s Roma attempted to control the game early on, rewarded for their dominance with a controversial penalty, as Gentiletti brought down Dzeko.   The referee awarded a penalty for the foul, though replays seem to suggest that the collision came outside of the box.  , though, did not think twice, despatching the penalty into the net after 10 minutes.   The first-half then fizzled out a little, with flashes of quality coming in the form of long-range strikes from Lazio’s Anderson and Roma’s Nainggolan that struck the woodwork.   The game was wrapped up for Roma in the second-half as   burst away from Basta, driving into the box and pushing his effort through Lazio goalkeeper Federico Marchetti.   From then on, Roma were comfortable, but second-half substitute Miroslav Klose could have pinched a goal for Lazio in the final minutes, though his effort cannoned off his right boot and over the bar. \n', '2015-11-08 15:55:00', 3),
	(7649, 'goal_en17110872', 'Niang: Donnarumma saved Milan against Atalanta', '', 'goal', 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/723/serie-a/2015/11/08/17110872/niang-donnarumma-saved-milan-against-atalanta', 'http://images.performgroup.com/di/library/omnisport/76/2c/gianluigidonnarumma-cropped_1e8gbaktxhrgn1ujq9ybjcjq57.jpg?t=-462539448&w=620&h=430', 'The striker hailed his 16-year-old team-mate for his display at San Siro on Saturday after he preserved a goalless draw despite a disappointing Rossoneri performance', 'Serie A,Milan,MBaye Niang,Gianluigi Donnarumma', 'en', 'The striker hailed his 16-year-old team-mate for his display at San Siro on Saturday after he preserved a goalless draw despite a disappointing Rossoneri performance \n \n \n \n  heaped praise on teenage goalkeeper   following  s draw with  , admitting his team-mates heroic display earned them a point. \n \nDonnarumma, 16, produced a performance beyond his years to thwart Atalanta and ensure Milan preserved a goalless draw on Saturday. \n \nThe Italy youth international made a number of saves in the second half, namely to deny Luca Cigarini, who drew a fine block from the youngster before firing the rebound over the crossbar. \n \nWe see every day what Donnarumma is capable of, Niang told the clubs official website. Today he saved us, we have to congratulate him and he deserves all the praise. \n \n \nThe match at San Siro was the first time Milan had dropped points since October 17, ending a run of three successive league wins. \n \nNiang added: We now have to go to Turin [to play Juventus] with the same mentality that we had for the match versus Lazio. \n \nWe have two weeks to prepare for the match against Juventus. \n  \n \n', '2015-11-08 16:21:00', 2),
	(7651, 'goal_en17112892', 'VIDEO: Man City should not be panicked into January signings by Villa stalemate', '', 'goal', 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/3194/video/2015/11/08/17112892/video-man-city-should-not-be-panicked-into-january-signings', '', 'The Blues failed to find the back of the net for the second time in three Premier League games, but Manuel Pellegrini put Sundays result down to bad luck - and its hard to argue', 'Premier League,Manchester City,Wilfried Bony,Manuel Pellegrini,Sergio Agüero', 'en', 'The Blues failed to find the back of the net for the second time in three Premier League games, but Manuel Pellegrini put Sundays result down to bad luck - and its hard to argue \n \n \n \n Manuel Pellegrini insists Manchester City should keep playing the same way after their second goalless draw in three Premier League games, and it is hard to argue with his sentiment... as much as Sundays stalemate with Aston Villa was a disappointment. A hamstring injury to Wilfried Bony, sustained during the first half, robbed City of a target man. With Sergio Aguero already out, Pellegrini opted for Jesus Navas to come off the bench rather than youngster Kelechi Iheanacho. Kevin De Bruyne and Raheem Sterling both filled in at No.9 at times but neither were able to break the deadlock when presented with gilt-edged chances. Fernando hit the bar with a close-range header at the death as Citys bad luck was compounded. It was, as Pellegrini admitted, one of those days. But would it have been if City had brought in another striker during the summer?  Even with Agueros injury history, it would have been tough to bring in another striker with Wilfried Bony, who had only joined for £25m plus six months earlier, waiting to take his chance and Iheanacho ready to come through. Especially given the £100m outlay on fellow forwards De Bruyne and Sterling, who have since shared the burden with both Aguero and Silva absent. A year ago City would not have been able to cope without those two; this time around theyve done it almost perfectly. Should City take action in January, then? The club are clearly pursuing big-name, big-money targets these days, and not many of those are available in winter. Bony has not entirely convinced over the last month or so - why risk another mid-season signing coming in, taking his time to settle and taking up a chunk of the summer transfer budget? Bigger players will be available come the off-season. Any City fans hoping for a January arrival should - unless Aguero suffers a serious set-back or fresh injury - be patient. I’m disappointed with the result but I have nothing to complain about my team, Pellegrini said. We played very well for the 90 minutes.  They [Villa] didn’t have one shot on our goal. It is not easy when you try to attack when you have 60 metres behind you and they are sitting back. “The first half we didn’t create one chance but after that we dominated the game. We were very unlucky with the three or four clear chances we had. We had an injury to our striker also at the beginning which is important in these type of games. “We tried different ways to score the goals but sometimes this happens in football and we couldn’t do it.” The manager is right on this one; the result should be put down to bad luck rather than bad judgement. \n \n', '2015-11-08 16:45:00', 1),
	(7652, 'goal_en2162540', 'TP Mazembe 2-0 USM Alger (agg. 4-1): Samatta, Assale seal Champions League triumph', '', 'goal', 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/89/africa/2015/11/08/17111852/tp-mazembe-2-0-usm-alger-agg-4-1-samatta-assale-seal', 'http://images.performgroup.com/di/library/omnisport/2d/f4/mbwana-ally-samat-cropped_1qdjweg9z47o9138re3r96kvl8.jpg?t=-410082544&w=620&h=430', 'The Congolese club secured their place at the Club World Cup, where they could face European champions Barcelona, by sealing a second-leg victory on Sunday', 'CAF Champions League,TP Mazembe,USM Alger', 'en', 'The Congolese club secured their place at the Club World Cup, where they could face European champions Barcelona, by sealing a second-leg victory on Sunday \n \n \n  clinched their fifth CAF Champions League title with a 2-0 win over   in the second leg of the final on Sunday. \n \nMbwana Ally Samattas second-half penalty and a late strike from Roger Assale sealed the 4-1 aggregate win for the dominant home side and ensured they will compete in the Club World Cup later this year. \n \nGoals from Rainford Kalaba and Samatta had put the Congolese in control of the tie heading into the second leg and Patrice Carterons side never looked likely to surrender their advantage. \n \nMazembe controlled the first half, though they struggled to create any meaningful chances against a USMA side who defended deep and looked to spring counter-attacks. \n \nAdama Traore missed a great chance to put Mazembe ahead early in the second term when he failed to hit the target following Samattas delivery, but they finally broke the deadlock on 74 minutes. \n \nFarouk Chafai was adjudged to have fouled substitute Assale in the penalty area despite appearing to make clean contact with the ball, allowing Samatta to convert from the spot to put Mazembe 3-1 up on aggregate and draw level with tournament top scorer Bakri Babeker with his seventh goal. \n \nUSMA pressed late on but there was ultimately no way back for the Algerians in their first ever appearance in the final, and Assale made certain of the victory when Samata set him up to score after a fast break in injury time. \n \nThe victory sees Mazembe secure a place in the Club World Cup, which will be held in Japan in December. \n \nEuropean champions Barcelona and Copa Libertadores winners River Plate have already sealed their place at the tournament along with Auckland City and Club America - the Champions League winners from Oceania and South America respectively. \n \nThe winner of the Asian continental tournament - either Al-Ahli or Guangzhou Evergrande - and the J-League champions will complete the list of contenders. \n  \n', '2015-11-08 16:53:00', 0),
	(7815, 'greatgoals2015-golden-boy-shortlist-features-players-from-liverpool-spurs-plus-anthony-martial-hecto', '2015 Golden Boy shortlist features players from Liverpool, Spurs plus Anthony Martial & Hector Belle', '', 'greatgoals', 'http://www.101greatgoals.com/blog/2015-golden-boy-shortlist-features-players-from-liverpool-spurs-plus-anthony-martial-hector-bellerin-list/', 'http://www.tuttosport.com/sondaggi/calcio/2015/11/06-5653085/vota_il_golden_boy_2015/?cookieAccept&cookieAccept', '2015 Golden Boy shortlist features players from Liverpool, Spurs plus Anthony Martial & Hector Bellerin [List]', '[uArsenal, uBarcelona, uChelsea, uLiverpool, uManchester City, uManchester United, uReal Madrid, uTottenham]', 'en', 'Who is the best young talent in Europe? That question is set to receive an answer shortly, after the nominees for the 2015 Golden Boy award have been released. The Golden Boy award has been established and run by Italian paper Tuttosport, however the voting is up to the public ( ). The only real qualification for the award is that only players under 21-years-old can be considered for the honour. 40 young footballers were included in the list, while thirteen of those players play their football in the Premier League. That said, only four Englishmen made the cut. Interestingly, last year’s winner Raheem Sterling didn’t even make the top 40 this time around, however a couple of his former Liverpool teammates were selected. Liverpool duo Jordon Ibe and Divock Origi were picked, while Manchester United also had two men included: Anthony Martial and Luke Shaw. Elsewhere, Tottenham’s Deli Alli and Arsenal’s Hector Bellerin are in, so too are Chelsea pair Nathan Ake and Ruben Loftus-Cheek. The full list, broken down by the different leagues players come from, is as follows: : Nathan Ake (Watford; on loan from Chelsea), Dele Alli (Tottenham), Héctor Bellerín (Arsenal), Jordon Ibe (Liverpool), Kelechi Iheanacho (Manchester City), Ruben Loftus-Cheek (Chelsea), Anthony Martial (Manchester United), Divock Origi (Liverpool), Luke Shaw (Manchester United), Adama Traoré (Aston Villa). : Marco Asensio (Espanyol), Zakaria Bakkali (Valencia), Ángel Correa (Atlético Madrid), Danilo Barbosa (Valencia), Munir El Haddadi (Barcelona), Alen Halilovic (Barcelona), Sandro Ramírez (Barcelona). : Kingsley Coman (Bayern Munich), Dahoud Mahmoud (Borussia M’gladbach), Francisco Rodríguez (Wolsfburg), Pierre-Emile Hojberg (Schalke), Adnan Januzaj (Borussia Dortmund; on loan from Manchester United), Max Meyer (Schalke), : Ricardo Kishna (Lazio), Sergej Milinkovic-Savic (Lazio), Alessio Romagnoli (Milan) : Mario Pasalic (Monaco; on loan from Chelsea), Adrien Rabiot (PSG), Adama Traoré (Monaco) : Jason Denayer (Galatasaray; on loan from Manchester City) : Anwar El Ghazi (Ajax Amsterdam), Gaston Pereiro (PSV), Tonny Vilhena (Feyenoord) : Goncalo Guedes (Benfica), Ruben Neves (Porto) : Nemanja Maksimovic (Astana) : Marko Pajca (Dinamo Zagreb) : Moses Simon (KAA Gent), Youri Tielemans (Anderlecht) : Andrija Zivkovic (Partizan Belgrade)', '2015-11-08 19:48:23', 0),
	(7894, 'greatgoalsthibaut-courtois-uploads-extended-footage-of-his-chelsea-rehab-exercises-on-facebook-video', 'Thibaut Courtois uploads extended footage of his Chelsea rehab exercises on Facebook (Video)', '', 'greatgoals', 'http://www.101greatgoals.com/blog/thibaut-courtois-uploads-extended-footage-of-his-chelsea-rehab-exercises-on-facebook-video/', 'http://www.101greatgoals.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-05-at-6.45.36-PM.png', 'Thibaut Courtois uploads extended footage of his Chelsea rehab exercises on Facebook (Video)', '[uChelsea, uThibaut Courtois]', 'en', 'The Blues are currently without their number one keeper Thibaut Courtois after the Belgium international tore his meniscus at training. The stopper has since gone under the knife, and by the looks of things his recovery is going well. Courtois has been keeping his fans up to date with his progress through social media, and today the Belgian stopper uploaded an extended video of his Chelsea rehab exercises on Facebook. Watch the video below. \n', '2015-11-05 20:06:05', 1),
